President Trump met with Gianni Infantino, the head of FIFA, to discuss the upcoming World Cup in 2026, which will be hosted by the United States, Mexico, and Canada. They also discussed initiatives to improve women's soccer. Trump stated that the peace talks with the Taliban are dead following an attack in which they killed 12 people, including an American soldier. He also mentioned the possibility of meeting with Iranian President Hassan Rouhani. Trump addressed various other topics, including gun control, illegal border crossings, judges, and the upcoming election in North Carolina. He denied mishandling classified information and expressed support for helping the Bahamas recover from a hurricane. Trump also commented on China, stating that the US is doing well and could hit a new stock market record, while China has suffered losses.